I'm trying to disable schema generation by default across all endpoints and enable it only on select few. The priority order in func `get_operation` of class `OpenAPISchemaGenerator` seems to achieve what I want. However, this does not work correctly when you've set `None` on `DEFAULT_AUTO_SCHEMA_CLASS` and `swagger_schema` but with a valid value for `auto_schema`.

```
# settings.py
SWAGGER_SETTINGS = {
    'DEFAULT_AUTO_SCHEMA_CLASS': None
}

# views.py
class ArticleViewSet(viewsets.ModelViewSet):
    swagger_schema = None

    @swagger_auto_schema(auto_schema=SwaggerAutoSchema)
    def create(self, request, *args, **kwargs):
        return super(...) 
```

The code never reaches [to the point where it evaluates the priority](https://github.com/axnsan12/drf-yasg/blob/23ebe2ff3eec19f0d7782462abf58ddcd49f7017/src/drf_yasg/generators.py#L361)  of inspector class for that endpoint because early on in the code that [endpoint is discarded](https://github.com/axnsan12/drf-yasg/blob/23ebe2ff3eec19f0d7782462abf58ddcd49f7017/src/drf_yasg/generators.py#L49)  because you set `None` on class-wide attr `swagger_schema`

