# xxx Support unicast for foreign device application
Implementing foreign device behavior in my BACnet application, I notice an major difference between explanation and
bacpypes implementation. In following page ([[http://www.bacnet.org/Tutorial/HMN-Overview/sld036.htm]]), the foreign
application can "talk with any BACnet device directly without registration". Only the broadcast exchange are blocked
until `RegisterForeignDevice` service is acknowledged by BBMD device.

My tests regarding this special case are failing with following debug logs:

```
2018-02-07 11:41:20,315 - DEBUG - bvll - decode - decode <PDU 10.33.74.62 -> 10.33.74.104 :
81.0a.00.0c.01.20.ff.ff.00.ff.10.08>
2018-02-07 11:41:20,318 - DEBUG - bvll - __init__ - __init__ () {}
2018-02-07 11:41:20,318 - DEBUG - bvll - __init__ - __init__ () {}
2018-02-07 11:41:20,319 - DEBUG - pdu - __init__ - __init__ () {}
2018-02-07 11:41:20,319 - DEBUG - pdu - __init__ -     - my_kwargs: {}
2018-02-07 11:41:20,319 - DEBUG - pdu - __init__ -     - other_kwargs: {}
2018-02-07 11:41:20,320 - DEBUG - comm - __init__ - __init__ () {}
2018-02-07 11:41:20,320 - DEBUG - comm - __init__ -     - my_kwargs: {}
2018-02-07 11:41:20,320 - DEBUG - comm - __init__ -     - other_kwargs: {}
2018-02-07 11:41:20,321 - DEBUG - comm - __init__ - __init__ None () {}
2018-02-07 11:41:20,321 - DEBUG - comm - response - response (<bacpypes.bvll.OriginalUnicastNPDU object at
0x7fdc3c46f890>,) {}
2018-02-07 11:41:20,321 - DEBUG - bvllservice - confirmation - confirmation <bacpypes.bvll.OriginalUnicastNPDU object
at 0x7fdc3c46f890>
2018-02-07 11:41:20,322 - DEBUG - bvllservice - confirmation -     - packet dropped, unregistered
```

After investigation I found the potential root cause in the `BIPForeign` class from `bvllservice.py` file. Indeed
`registrationStatus` is checked before analyse if request is unicast or broadcast. This check is done in
`confirmation` and `indication` methods.

I suggest to check `registrationStatus` only for non unicast request.
See patch attached.

[0019_UnicastToForeign.txt](https://github.com/JoelBender/bacpypes/files/1711624/0019_UnicastToForeign.txt)

Sketch:
```python
class DatabaseFactory(object):
    def __init__(self, objects: dict, db: Any = None) -> None:
        """
        :param objects: Dictionary of models and description of ones.
        :param db: Optional parameter if you are using Flask with SQLAlchemy.
        """
        self.objects = objects
        self.db = db

    def start(self, records_count: int = 20) -> None:
        for model, fields in self.objects.items():

            count = fields.get('__count__', records_count)
            locale = fields.get('__locale__', config.DEFAULT_LOCALE)

            field = Field(locale)

            if inspect.isclass(model):
                for i in range(count):
                    kwargs = dict()
                    if isinstance(fields, dict):
                        for a, b in fields.items():
                            if isinstance(b, dict):
                                field_name = b.get('method')
                                extra_kwargs = b.get('kwargs')
                                if not a.startswith('__'):
                                    if field_name is Ellipsis:
                                        field_name = a
                                    kwargs.setdefault(a, field(field_name, **extra_kwargs))
                            else:
                                if not a.startswith('__'):
                                    if b is Ellipsis:
                                        b = a
                                    kwargs.setdefault(a, field(b))
                    else:
                        raise ValueError('You should describe attributes of model')
                    try:
                        if self.db is not None:
                            obj = model(**kwargs or {})
                            self.db.session.add(obj)
                            self.db.session.commit()
                        else:
                            model.objects.create(**kwargs or {})
                    except Exception:
                        raise TypeError('Class must be a Django Model.')
            else:
                raise TypeError('Model must be a class.')
```

It works fine for Django. Should work for Flask too, but I have not tested it yet.

```bash
$ pip install wrapt
```
Will fail in Windows using a Visual Studio in some languages, because it will try to output some accented characters, and pip will fail with ``UnicodeDecodeError`` to decode them properly, and wrapt will not be properly installed.

```
Exception:
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "c:\users\memsharded\envs\conan3\lib\site-packages\pip\compat\__init__.py", line 73, in console_to_str
    return s.decode(sys.__stdout__.encoding)
UnicodeDecodeError: 'utf-8' codec can't decode byte 0xf3 in position 11: invalid continuation byte
```

The failure is in ``pip/compat/__init__.py`` file:

```python
if sys.version_info >= (3,):
    def console_to_str(s):
        try:
            return s.decode(sys.__stdout__.encoding)
        except UnicodeDecodeError:
               return s.decode('utf_8')
```

I have just workarounded it with:

```python
if sys.version_info >= (3,):
    def console_to_str(s):
        try:
            return s.decode(sys.__stdout__.encoding)
        except UnicodeDecodeError:
            try:
               return s.decode('utf_8')
            except Exception as e:
               return "Cannot decode this string"
```

It seems this will be improved in pip 10 (not yet released): https://github.com/pypa/pip/issues/4110#issuecomment-304476523

