## Minimum reproducible example
```java
    NDArray ndInput = NDArray.array(mapInput(history),
                new Shape(new ArrayBuffer<>().$plus$eq(1).$plus$eq(this.inMap.size())), Context.cpu(0));
    ArrayBuffer<NDArray> dataTemp = new ArrayBuffer<NDArray>().$plus$eq(ndInput);
    NDArrayIter data = new NDArrayIter(dataTemp, new ArrayBuffer<>(), 1, false, "discard", "data",  null);
    ---> this.model.bind(DataDesc.ListMap2Descs(data.provideData()),
            Option.apply(null), false, false, true, Option.apply(null), "write");
    this.model.initParams(new Uniform(0.01f), null, null, true, false);
    float[] out = this.model.predict(data, 1, true).head().toArray();
```

* The function call mapInput(history) returns a flat Java array of floating point values the same size as inMap.size() (I have verified this is working as I expect)
* The NDArray's dimensions should be 1 x inMap.size() (batch of 1 x the number of features).
*  this.model is the Module that was loaded with the Module.loadCheckpoint() method, I have verified the model loads from file properly
* ---> indicates the line in my code that the error is occurring on
* I am loading a model which was trained using the Python package
* The model relies on a custom loss function, I have re-implemented the loss function as a CustomOp that simply forwards the input to it along (no need to calculate loss here since my use case is only performing predictions, never back prop)

For context here is the loss:
```java
public class MyLoss extends CustomOp {

    @Override
    public void forward(final boolean isTrain, final String[] req, final NDArray[] inData, final NDArray[] outData,
                        final NDArray[] aux)
    {
        //No need to calculate loss, just copy predictions forward, which are in the first NDArray in inData
        assign(outData[0], req[0], inData[0]);
    }

    @Override
    public void backward(final String[] req, final NDArray[] outGrad, final NDArray[] inData, final NDArray[] outData,
                         final NDArray[] inGrad, final NDArray[] aux)
    {
        //Doesn't require implementation for forward prop
    }
}
```
And it's corresponding property:
```java
public class MyProp extends CustomOpProp {

    /**
     * Constructor for MyProp used to load model
     */
    public MyProp() {
        super(false);
    }

    @Override
    public CustomOp createOperator(final String ctx, final int[][] inShapes, final int[] inDtypes) {
        return new MyLoss();
    }

    @Override
    public Tuple3<Shape[], Shape[], Shape[]> inferShape(Shape[] inShape) {
        return new Tuple3<>(inShape, new Shape[]{inShape[0]}, new Shape[0]);
    }

    @Override
    public String[] listArguments() {
        return new String[]{"data", "label"};
    }

    @Override
    public String[] listOutputs() {
        return new String[]{"preds"};
    }

}
```

